Carbon Credit Coins (CCC) is a blockchain-based digital asset designed to enhance transparency, traceability, and accessibility within the global carbon credit market.

The project aims to address structural inefficiencies such as lack of transparency, limited access, and risks of double counting in traditional carbon systems.

CCC integrates environmental documentation, certification records, and publicly accessible data to provide a verifiable and transparent ecosystem. All relevant information is made available through official channels, enabling independent verification by participants.

The project is supported by environmental records, audit documentation, and a publicly disclosed reserve structure, reinforcing its commitment to transparency and accountability.

CCC is designed to bridge environmental assets with digital finance, contributing to a more efficient, accessible, and responsible global carbon economy.
